  "finding": "Against 183132 held-out high-amplitude B2 duplicate rows, the P07d-style corrections do not improve odd-channel charge closure: raw charge res68 is 0.1208, traditional is 0.1208, and ML is 0.1764. Timing closure is also worse after correction: raw abs68 is 0.148 ns, traditional is 0.149 ns, and ML is 0.221 ns. The duplicate readout therefore does not support applying the ratio-transfer correction to real high-amplitude B2 pulses as a closure improvement.",
